---
alwaysApply: true
globs: "**/*.ts"
---

# NESTJS RULES

- Use modular architecture
- One responsibility per service/controller

# CONTROLLERS

- Thin controllers only:
  - no business logic
  - only request/response mapping

# SERVICES

- Business logic lives here
- Keep services stateless where possible

# DEPENDENCY INJECTION

- Use constructor injection (Nest standard)
- Avoid circular dependencies

# DATA ACCESS

- Repositories or data access layer required
- Never access DB directly in controllers

# ERROR HANDLING

- Use NestJS exceptions:
  - BadRequestException
  - NotFoundException
  - InternalServerErrorException

# VALIDATION

- Use DTOs with class-validator
- Validate all external input

# MODULE DESIGN

- Feature-based modules preferred
- Avoid shared “god modules”